# Windows Technical Support Lab

## Project Overview

Designed and implemented hands-on Windows environment using VirtualBox to simulate real-world Technical Support Engineer responsibilities.
The projects focused on user administration, system troubleshooting, service management, networking, incident handling, and technical documentation.

---

### Environment

* Windows 11 Pro
* VirtualBox

### Activities Performed

* Created and managed local user accounts.
* Performed password reset procedures.
* Disabled and re-enabled user accounts.
* Investigated Windows logs using Event Viewer.
* Troubleshot Windows services including Print Spooler.
* Performed network diagnostics using ipconfig, ping, and nslookup.
* Verified internet connectivity and DNS resolution.
* Simulated support incidents and documented resolutions.

### Skills Demonstrated

* Windows Administration
* Account Management
* Password Management
* Event Viewer Analysis
* Service Troubleshooting
* Network Diagnostics
* Incident Handling

---

## Key Technical Skills Acquired

* Windows 11 Administration
* Ubuntu Linux Administration
* User and Access Management
* Password Reset Procedures
* Apache Web Server Administration
* MariaDB Database Management
* SSH Configuration
* Service Monitoring and Troubleshooting
* Event Viewer Investigation
* DNS and Network Troubleshooting
* Technical Documentation
* Incident Management

---

## Outcome

Successfully built and administered Windows environment that simulate common Technical Support Engineer tasks, including user management,
troubleshooting, network diagnostics, service recovery, incident handling, and system administration.
